{"id":21855,"date":"2020-04-26T05:03:00","date_gmt":"2020-04-26T04:03:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=21855"},"modified":"2021-10-26T12:40:04","modified_gmt":"2021-10-26T11:40:04","slug":"luang-prabang","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/laos\/luang-prabang\/","title":{"rendered":"11 Best Things To Do in Luang Prabang"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"todo\">Day 1 &#x2013; Peaceful Luang Prabang<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Start the trip at a slow pace. Luang Prabang is a<strong> <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/destinations\/best-unesco-world-heritage-sites\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">UNESCO world heritage<\/a> site and, as a result, all trucks and buses are banned from the city center. Enjoy the peacefulness, and serenity, on day 1!<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3>1. Watch the Monks Almsgiving ceremony<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Every morning, at sunrise, hundreds of barefooted Buddhist monks leave their temple. Lined-up, they walk down the streets in their saffron-colored garments, collecting sticky rice donations from the local people. Alms-giving, or Tak Bat, is an important and meaningful part of Laos&#x2019; culture and is an essential thing to do, while in Luang Prabang.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--hotels \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/luang-prabang-hotels-all\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" data-rich-text-format-boundary=\"true\">See all hotels to stay in Luang Prabang<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-582x810.jpg\" alt=\"Monks Almsgiving laos\"><\/noscript><img width=\"243\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Monks Almsgiving laos\" data-id=\"22951\" data-full-url=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos.jpg\" data-link=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?attachment_id=22951\" class=\"wp-image-22951 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 582px) 100vw, 582px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-582x810.jpg 582w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-300x417.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-600x835.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-431x600.jpg 431w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-243x338.jpg 243w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-1104x1536.jpg 1104w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-22x30.jpg 22w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-117x163.jpg 117w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120630\/Monks-Almsgiving-laos-129x180.jpg 129w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/231206