lank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120627\/Monks-ceremony-luang-prabang-laos-588x810.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure><\/li><\/ul><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>Observing and participating is allowed, but it is important to act respectfully. Therefore, follow these following guidelines:&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Dress appropriately- shoulders, chest, and legs should be covered.<\/li><li>Observe from a distance- don&#x2019;t walk into the way of the monks, and make sure flash is turned off on your camera.<\/li><li>Make sure to stay absolutely silent- enjoy the serenity!<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Time &amp; <a href=\"https:\/\/goo.gl\/maps\/FwKN5UjNNiqtsCV99\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Location<\/a> of almsgiving: Every day around 6 AM at Sakkaline Street. Ask your hotel for the exact timing for that day.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120634\/Monks-Almsgiving-ceremony-luang-prabang.jpg\" alt=\"Monks Almsgiving ceremony luang prabang\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"300\" alt=\"Monks Almsgiving ceremony luang prabang\" class=\"wp-image-22950 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120634\/Monks-Almsgiving-ceremony-luang-prabang.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120634\/Monks-Almsgiving-ceremony-luang-prabang-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23120634\/Monks-Almsgiving-ceremony-luang-prabang-600x400.jpg 60